content:
We need to analyze case. Recurrent fever, serositis (abdominal pain, chest pain with pleuritic), arthralgia, Mediterranean descent, autosomal dominant family history. Likely Familial Mediterranean Fever (FMF). Onset childhood, attacks last 1-3 days, every 2-3 weeks. Labs show inflammation. Genetic testing pending for MEFV mutations. So primary diagnosis FMF (ICD-10 M04.1? Actually FMF is M04.1 "Familial Mediterranean fever"). Provide confidence high, say 0.95.

Differential: 1) TNF receptor-associated periodic syndrome (TRAPS) - similar but longer attacks, may have periorbital edema. Provide lower confidence 0.3. 2) Hyper IgD syndrome (Mevalonate kinase deficiency) - episodes with fever, abdominal pain, but usually early onset, high IgD. Confidence 0.2. 3) Acute rheumatic fever? but less likely. Maybe systemic juvenile idiopathic arthritis (Still's disease) - but chronic. Provide confidence 0.15. 4) Periodic fever, aphthous stomatitis, pharyngitis, adenitis (PFAPA) - but child, not adult. Provide low confidence 0.1. Might need 3-5 diff; we can give 4.

Key findings: recurrent short fever episodes, serositis (peritonitis, pleuritis), arthritis, Mediterranean ancestry, autosomal dominant family history, normal between attacks.

Tests: 1) Serum amyloid A (SAA) level (routine) to assess risk. 2) Genetic testing for MEFV mutations (immediate/urgent). 3) Complete blood count, CRP, ESR (routine). 4) Abdominal ultrasound during attack (urgent). 5) Echocardiogram? Not needed.

Management: Immediate: treat acute attack with colchicine (but prophylactic). Actually colchicine is main therapy prophylactic; for acute attack, NSAIDs and colchicine can help. So immediate: NSAID for pain. Medications: Colchicine 0.6 mg orally twice daily (adjust for weight/renal). For colchicine-resistant, consider IL-1 inhibitors (anakinra 100 mg subcut daily) or canakinumab. Provide doses.

Consultations: Rheumatology (urgent), Genetic counseling (routine). Possibly Gastroenterology for abdominal pain.

Red flags: Development of amyloidosis (proteinuria), persistent high fever, atypical features like rash, neurological signs, signs of infection, uncontrolled hypertension, etc.

Now produce JSON only.

Check format: primary_diagnosis object with name, confidence, icd_code.

Differential list each with name, confidence, icd_code.

Key_findings array of strings.

Tests array objects with test and priority values exactly "immediate|urgent|routine". Use lower-case? The spec says values exactly those strings. Use "immediate", "urgent", "routine".

Management: immediate array of strings (actions). medications array of strings "drug: dose, route". Provide colon separated.

consultations array strings "specialty: urgency". Use "rheumatology: urgent".

Red_flags array strings.

Now produce JSON. Ensure proper commas, no trailing commas.

Let's craft.



